Question:
A = {x : x ∈ R ir x² - (a+b)x + ab = 0},
B = {1, 2} ir C = {2, 4, 5}
įrodykite, kad P(B ∩ C) = P(B) ∩ P(C)

Solution:
Reikia parodyti, kad } -(\underline{a} + \underline{b}) = -\underline{a} - \underline{b}
\text{Dabar, } -(\underline{a} + \underline{b}) = (-1) (\underline{a} + \underline{b})
= (-1) \underline{a} + (-1) \underline{b} \text{ [distributyvumo dėsnis]}
= -\underline{a} - \underline{b}
\therefore -(\underline{a} + \underline{b}) = -\underline{a} - \underline{b} \text{ (Parodyta)}

\text{ Duota, } \underline{a} + \underline{b} = \underline{c}
\text{Reikia parodyti, kad } \underline{a} = \underline{c} - \underline{b}
\text{Duota, } \underline{a} + \underline{b} = \underline{c}
\text{arba, } \underline{a} + \underline{b} - \underline{b} = \underline{c} - \underline{b} \text{ [abiejose pusėse pridedame } (-\underline{b}) \text{]}
\text{arba, } \underline{a} + \underline{0} = \underline{c} - \underline{b}
\therefore \underline{a} = \underline{c} - \underline{b}
\text{Atvirkščiai,}
\underline{a} = \underline{c} - \underline{b}
\text{arba, } \underline{a} + \underline{b} = \underline{c} - \underline{b} + \underline{b} \text{ [abiejose pusėse pridedame } \underline{b} \text{ ]}
= \underline{c} + \underline{0}
\therefore \underline{a} + \underline{b} = \underline{c}
\therefore \text{ Jei } \underline{a} + \underline{b} = \underline{c} \text{ tada, } \underline{a} = \underline{c} - \underline{b} \text{ ir atvirkščiai. (Parodyta)}

